<article>
    <h1>4G In&#xAD;ter&#xAD;net restored in parts of Kash&#xAD;mir</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200818/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-18"><time>2020-08-18</time></a>
        - <span>WORLD</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>SRINAGAR • In­dia has restored high-speed 4G In­ter­net ser­vices in two districts of Kash­mir af­ter the Supreme Court last month said an in­def­i­nite shut­down of the In­ter­net there was il­le­gal.</p>
    <p>The com­mu­ni­ca­tions lock­down had been im­posed af­ter par­tial au­ton­omy of the Mus­lim-ma­jor­ity re­gion was scrapped by Prime Min­is­ter Naren­dra Modi last year.</p>
    <p>The au­thor­i­ties had said the se­cu­rity sit­u­a­tion was not con­ducive to restor­ing mo­bile In­ter­net access.</p>
    <p>“The high-speed mo­bile data ser­vices in the districts of Ganderbal and Udhampur shall be restored forth­with, on a trial ba­sis,” a govern­ment state­ment said on Sun­day, adding that In­ter­net speed would con­tinue to be curbed in other cities.</p>


